1
00:00:00,918 --> 00:00:03,002
♪

2
00:00:09,927 --> 00:00:12,805
[wind blowing]

3
00:00:14,682 --> 00:00:17,142
- [creaking]
- [Coco gasps softly]

4
00:00:19,812 --> 00:00:21,313
Is that the wind?

5
00:00:24,316 --> 00:00:26,151
- [QIFREY] Ah, you're awake.
- Huh?

6
00:00:26,694 --> 00:00:27,862
[Qifrey grunts softly]

7
00:00:28,069 --> 00:00:30,655
I took the liberty of hailing us
a Pegasus Carriage.

8
00:00:30,656 --> 00:00:31,657
[COCO] Huh?

9
00:00:31,949 --> 00:00:33,157
You must be chilly,

10
00:00:33,158 --> 00:00:35,034
flying so high
in your bedclothes.

11
00:00:35,577 --> 00:00:37,412
Our ride's almost over.

12
00:00:38,706 --> 00:00:40,790
- Oh, look there.
- [Coco gasps]

13
00:00:40,791 --> 00:00:42,416
Our destination.

14
00:00:42,417 --> 00:00:43,794
[Coco gasps]

15
00:00:44,294 --> 00:00:45,754
[gasps]

16
00:00:46,505 --> 00:00:48,215
♪

17
00:00:51,969 --> 00:00:54,220
[QIFREY] That is my atelier.

18
00:00:54,221 --> 00:00:57,016
And your new place of study.

19
00:00:58,308 --> 00:01:00,686
[♪ opening theme song playing]

20
00:02:31,526 --> 00:02:33,527
[QIFREY] Don't worry
about your house.

21
00:02:33,528 --> 00:02:35,906
I planted Guard Briar seeds
all around it.

22
00:02:36,573 --> 00:02:38,783
They'll grow quickly,
and as they do,

23
00:02:38,784 --> 00:02:40,952
they'll form
a protective barrier.

24
00:02:40,953 --> 00:02:43,370
The spell that petrified
your house,

25
00:02:43,371 --> 00:02:45,372
is presently unknown to us.

26
00:02:45,373 --> 00:02:47,249
Best to keep
any careless visitors

27
00:02:47,250 --> 00:02:48,460
from getting too close.

28
00:02:53,924 --> 00:02:55,424
Well, then...

29
00:02:55,425 --> 00:02:56,593
Uh?

30
00:02:57,302 --> 00:02:58,595
Coco?

31
00:03:03,600 --> 00:03:05,183
What's the matter?

32
00:03:05,184 --> 00:03:07,103
[crying]
I promised my mother

33
00:03:07,104 --> 00:03:10,439
that I would never leave her
all alone,

34
00:03:10,440 --> 00:03:11,859
and now, I...

35
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:13,735
Oh, dear.

36
00:03:18,197 --> 00:03:20,575
Please don't blame yourself.

37
00:03:20,951 --> 00:03:22,327
You didn't know.

38
00:03:26,331 --> 00:03:28,750
[door closes]

39
00:03:29,584 --> 00:03:31,210
[footsteps]

40
00:03:31,503 --> 00:03:32,754
♪

41
00:03:35,132 --> 00:03:37,342
[QIFREY] Here,
to wash your face.

42
00:03:37,926 --> 00:03:41,346
Let your tears fall behind you,
and look forward.

43
00:03:43,557 --> 00:03:46,518
As of today,
this shall be your home.

44
00:03:47,769 --> 00:03:49,228
[Coco gasps]

45
00:03:53,775 --> 00:03:55,610
[COCO] Uh...

46
00:03:56,862 --> 00:04:00,198
- [COCO] Um, what is this?
- [QIFREY] Hm?

47
00:04:00,199 --> 00:04:01,657
Why, it's water.

48
00:04:01,658 --> 00:04:03,534
Oh, right.

49
00:04:03,535 --> 00:04:05,953
How could I forget?
You'll need a change of clothes.

50
00:04:05,954 --> 00:04:07,872
[COCO] Water isn't usually
so round and floaty.

51
00:04:07,873 --> 00:04:09,582
- I'll be back in a flash.
- [gasps]

52
00:04:09,583 --> 00:04:11,584
Wait, could you explain

53
00:04:11,585 --> 00:04:13,587
how I'm supposed
to use this first?

54
00:04:14,295 --> 00:04:16,090
Mr. Qifrey?

55
00:04:18,175 --> 00:04:20,218
Touching magic
I know nothing about

56
00:04:20,219 --> 00:04:21,802
is a little scary now.

57
00:04:21,803 --> 00:04:23,722
[GIRL] Aw, don't be scared!

58
00:04:24,139 --> 00:04:26,892
Far as spells go,
that one's pretty simple.

59
00:04:27,142 --> 00:04:28,351
[chuckles]

60
00:04:29,268 --> 00:04:32,189
I can tell you all about it
if you want me to!

61
00:04:33,815 --> 00:04:34,982
[Coco gasps softly]

62
00:04:34,983 --> 00:04:37,443
What you've got there
is a Vapor Bubble.

63
00:04:37,444 --> 00:04:40,278
It's a kind of magic that takes
moisture out of the air

64
00:04:40,279 --> 00:04:41,655
and turns it into water.

65
00:04:41,656 --> 00:04:43,199
Hold out your hands for me.

66
00:04:43,200 --> 00:04:44,451
Here! Go on!

67
00:04:45,619 --> 00:04:47,787
You tilt the lower tray
like this,

68
00:04:47,788 --> 00:04:49,663
and the water comes flowing out!

69
00:04:49,664 --> 00:04:53,375
Wow, amazing.
Thanks so much.

70
00:04:53,376 --> 00:04:55,544
- Thank you!
- [COCO] Huh?

71
00:04:55,545 --> 00:04:58,672
I always love it so when
people tell me "thank you."

72
00:04:58,673 --> 00:05:00,674
So thank you for your thanks!

73
00:05:00,675 --> 00:05:02,802
[COCO] Oh, I see.

74
00:05:02,803 --> 00:05:05,805
Well, thank you, again.

75
00:05:05,806 --> 00:05:06,973
And thank you!

76
00:05:06,974 --> 00:05:08,682
That one's
for thanking me again!

77
00:05:08,683 --> 00:05:11,309
Thank you too!
Thank you for thanking me

78
00:05:11,310 --> 00:05:13,229
- for thanking you.
- [GIRL 2] Stop responding,

79
00:05:13,230 --> 00:05:15,023
- just ignore her.
- [both gasp]

80
00:05:16,315 --> 00:05:19,277
She'll tire herself out
and give up.

81
00:05:19,278 --> 00:05:21,279
Richeh, you're so mean!

82
00:05:21,280 --> 00:05:23,363
I was actually being
very helpful,

83
00:05:23,364 --> 00:05:24,740
I'll have you know.

84
00:05:24,741 --> 00:05:25,992
[Coco gasps]

85
00:05:25,993 --> 00:05:27,911
[COCO] The pen and ink.

86
00:05:28,912 --> 00:05:31,747
Would the two of you
happen to be witches?

87
00:05:31,748 --> 00:05:33,291
We're apprentices.

88
00:05:33,292 --> 00:05:35,709
Students studying
with Master Qifrey.

89
00:05:35,710 --> 00:05:38,254
Wait, if you're asking,
then are you not?

90
00:05:38,255 --> 00:05:39,463
So what are you?

91
00:05:39,464 --> 00:05:41,507
Are you the same age
as Richeh and I?

92
00:05:41,508 --> 00:05:43,217
Are you? Looks like it.

93
00:05:43,218 --> 00:05:45,343
And what atelier
did you come here from?

94
00:05:45,344 --> 00:05:46,679
[Coco exhales nervously]

95
00:05:46,680 --> 00:05:49,140
Well, uh, I think
it's still a little early

96
00:05:49,141 --> 00:05:50,641
to call myself a student.

97
00:05:50,642 --> 00:05:52,434
The truth is, before yesterday,

98
00:05:52,435 --> 00:05:55,021
I had never drawn
a spell in my life.

99
00:05:55,022 --> 00:05:57,274
But I do live here
starting today.

100
00:05:58,775 --> 00:06:00,277
[BOTH] Oh...

101
00:06:01,069 --> 00:06:02,486
What is it?

102
00:06:02,487 --> 00:06:03,904
So it's you.

103
00:06:03,905 --> 00:06:05,698
You're the one
that rumor's about?

104
00:06:05,699 --> 00:06:08,035
What do you mean?
What rumor?

105
00:06:08,952 --> 00:06:10,453
[exclaims softly]

106
00:06:10,578 --> 00:06:12,413
♪

107
00:06:16,084 --> 00:06:19,962
[GIRL] People have been
talking about an Outsider

108
00:06:19,963 --> 00:06:22,464
who made use of forbidden magic,

109
00:06:22,465 --> 00:06:25,218
and was then allowed
to become an apprentice

110
00:06:25,219 --> 00:06:27,386
with her memories intact.

111
00:06:28,096 --> 00:06:29,931
- [QIFREY] Coco?
- [Coco gasps]

112
00:06:31,099 --> 00:06:32,474
Are you all right?

113
00:06:32,475 --> 00:06:33,851
I think so.

114
00:06:33,852 --> 00:06:36,145
Looks as though you've all been
getting acquainted

115
00:06:36,146 --> 00:06:37,313
with each other.

116
00:06:37,314 --> 00:06:39,565
Richeh, Tetia,
once you're finished helping

117
00:06:39,566 --> 00:06:42,068
with the morning chores,
will you go study in your rooms?

118
00:06:42,069 --> 00:06:43,820
- All right!
- Hm.

119
00:06:44,487 --> 00:06:47,531
[QIFREY] Here. It's what
all my students wear.

120
00:06:47,532 --> 00:06:48,742
[Coco exclaims softly]

121
00:06:50,035 --> 00:06:51,785
Please don't worry.

122
00:06:51,786 --> 00:06:53,580
I will explain everything.

123
00:06:54,164 --> 00:06:55,582
[birds chirping]

124
00:06:56,166 --> 00:06:58,168
[QIFREY]
Looks like a perfect fit.

125
00:06:58,668 --> 00:06:59,920
[Coco exhales softly]

126
00:07:00,461 --> 00:07:03,923
And now, I shall share with you
the history of magic.

127
00:07:03,924 --> 00:07:06,009
[Coco gasps softly] Hm.

128
00:07:07,510 --> 00:07:09,178
[QIFREY] Long ago...

129
00:07:09,179 --> 00:07:11,680
magic was a part
of ordinary life.

130
00:07:11,681 --> 00:07:13,307
[scribbling]

131
00:07:13,308 --> 00:07:15,268
All that one needed to use it

132
00:07:15,269 --> 00:07:18,230
was a special ink
and a set of patterns.

133
00:07:19,273 --> 00:07:20,690
♪

134
00:07:23,610 --> 00:07:25,819
[QIFREY] It was a simple,
familiar tool,

135
00:07:25,820 --> 00:07:28,573
available to anyone
and everyone.

136
00:07:30,117 --> 00:07:32,034
Yet at the same time,

137
00:07:32,035 --> 00:07:34,745
it was a constant source
of conflict.

138
00:07:34,746 --> 00:07:36,538
[faint clamoring]

139
00:07:36,539 --> 00:07:39,917
[QIFREY] When mankind holds
the power to do anything,

140
00:07:39,918 --> 00:07:41,710
"anything" is what they do.

141
00:07:41,711 --> 00:07:44,714
Many horrific spells
were created.

142
00:07:48,843 --> 00:07:51,553
The few good souls
who remained in the world

143
00:07:51,554 --> 00:07:53,639
renounced war and strife,

144
00:07:53,640 --> 00:07:55,975
and banded together
as witches.

145
00:07:55,976 --> 00:07:58,894
They stole away
humanity's memory of magic,

146
00:07:58,895 --> 00:08:01,021
letting it only be known
to their disciples,

147
00:08:01,022 --> 00:08:02,899
who were sworn to protect it.

148
00:08:04,192 --> 00:08:06,569
That was the Day of the Pact.

149
00:08:07,028 --> 00:08:08,654
Since then,
people have believed

150
00:08:08,655 --> 00:08:12,158
that magic is a power
only a chosen few can wield.

151
00:08:12,159 --> 00:08:14,034
If the truth came to light,

152
00:08:14,035 --> 00:08:16,830
the world would fall
into chaos once again.

153
00:08:17,831 --> 00:08:20,166
You see, that's why
we've taken such care

154
00:08:20,167 --> 00:08:21,583
to preserve the secret.

155
00:08:21,584 --> 00:08:23,837
And why your story
has traveled so quickly.

156
00:08:24,545 --> 00:08:25,796
I'm sorry.

157
00:08:25,797 --> 00:08:26,964
No.

158
00:08:26,965 --> 00:08:29,092
I've brought
all this upon myself.

159
00:08:29,468 --> 00:08:30,635
But...

160
00:08:31,261 --> 00:08:33,096
What is "forbidden magic"?

161
00:08:34,513 --> 00:08:36,849
Magic drawn
during the age of war,

162
00:08:36,850 --> 00:08:39,436
and banished upon
the Day of the Pact.

163
00:08:40,187 --> 00:08:42,188
Magic for hurting people.

164
00:08:42,189 --> 00:08:43,231
[Coco gasps]

165
00:08:44,691 --> 00:08:46,692
[COCO] Teach me, I beg you!

166
00:08:46,693 --> 00:08:48,861
Let me learn about
this Forbidden Magic!

167
00:08:48,862 --> 00:08:51,114
I need to understand it!

168
00:08:51,739 --> 00:08:54,116
I can't go on not knowing.

169
00:08:54,117 --> 00:08:56,203
It's too frightening to bear!

170
00:08:57,120 --> 00:09:00,580
Normally, I tell my students
not to rush themselves,

171
00:09:00,581 --> 00:09:02,667
but I fear
it's too late for that.

172
00:09:05,295 --> 00:09:06,587
Come with me.

173
00:09:11,426 --> 00:09:13,593
There are any number
of forbidden spells

174
00:09:13,594 --> 00:09:15,638
I could list.
But to keep it simple,

175
00:09:16,348 --> 00:09:17,932
it's like so...

176
00:09:18,517 --> 00:09:21,268
Any spell cast directly
upon the human body

177
00:09:21,269 --> 00:09:23,063
is utterly prohibited.

178
00:09:23,480 --> 00:09:26,899
This includes transformation,
age alteration,

179
00:09:26,900 --> 00:09:30,319
teleportation without the use
of doors or conveyances.

180
00:09:30,320 --> 00:09:32,821
Manipulating thoughts
or emotions,

181
00:09:32,822 --> 00:09:35,325
doing harm to a person,
or healing them.

182
00:09:36,201 --> 00:09:38,286
There is but one exception.

183
00:09:38,828 --> 00:09:41,038
Erasing people's memories?

184
00:09:41,039 --> 00:09:42,748
[QIFREY] Precisely...

185
00:09:42,749 --> 00:09:46,836
Therefore, most spells
are cast on tools.

186
00:09:49,047 --> 00:09:51,425
Like carriages, or lamps.

187
00:09:52,800 --> 00:09:54,761
[gasps] Wow.

188
00:09:58,014 --> 00:10:01,851
Or even windows,
such as this one.

189
00:10:21,079 --> 00:10:23,081
It's a lake!

190
00:10:23,540 --> 00:10:26,917
But we were surrounded by hills
just a moment ago.

191
00:10:26,918 --> 00:10:28,961
[QIFREY] This is a Windowway.

192
00:10:28,962 --> 00:10:32,465
It links two round windows
bearing the same pattern.

193
00:10:32,466 --> 00:10:34,717
Do you see that building
in the distance?

194
00:10:35,718 --> 00:10:37,511
The Tower of Tomes.

195
00:10:37,512 --> 00:10:39,555
Every time a book on magic
is written,

196
00:10:39,556 --> 00:10:41,515
a copy instantly appears there,

197
00:10:41,516 --> 00:10:43,934
to ensure the knowledge within
is never lost.

198
00:10:43,935 --> 00:10:44,935
[Coco gasps]

199
00:10:44,936 --> 00:10:46,812
They'll have the picture book.

200
00:10:46,813 --> 00:10:48,105
Please take me there!

201
00:10:48,106 --> 00:10:49,940
I'll search nonstop
till I find it!

202
00:10:49,941 --> 00:10:51,024
Slow down.

203
00:10:51,025 --> 00:10:52,985
[water gushing]

204
00:10:52,986 --> 00:10:55,238
[rumbling]

205
00:11:00,619 --> 00:11:02,620
- [Qifrey grunts]
- [Coco exclaims]

206
00:11:02,621 --> 00:11:04,331
[Coco groans]

207
00:11:05,706 --> 00:11:07,000
♪

208
00:11:07,584 --> 00:11:10,629
[chuckles]
That's the Librarians' Trial.

209
00:11:11,338 --> 00:11:14,298
The Tower of Tomes is guarded
by four librarians,

210
00:11:14,299 --> 00:11:16,467
and only witches
who overcome their trials

211
00:11:16,468 --> 00:11:18,052
are allowed to enter.

212
00:11:18,512 --> 00:11:21,889
So if you wish to visit,
you're going to have to study.

213
00:11:22,849 --> 00:11:23,891
Coco...

214
00:11:24,518 --> 00:11:27,019
Hearing of your
eagerness to learn

215
00:11:27,020 --> 00:11:29,063
truly filled me with happiness.

216
00:11:29,897 --> 00:11:32,025
And the fear you feel
is natural.

217
00:11:32,691 --> 00:11:33,776
But...

218
00:11:35,028 --> 00:11:37,738
the spells which have
not been forbidden...

219
00:11:42,452 --> 00:11:46,122
are the ones that bring
happiness to people's lives.

220
00:11:46,498 --> 00:11:47,998
Don't you think

221
00:11:47,999 --> 00:11:50,459
you'd rather learn about
a gentler kind of magic?

222
00:11:50,460 --> 00:11:52,545
- [Coco gasps]
- [QIFREY] What do you say?

223
00:11:52,546 --> 00:11:53,546
[COCO] Huh?

224
00:11:53,547 --> 00:11:55,298
Are you interested?

225
00:11:55,798 --> 00:11:57,007
Yes.

226
00:11:57,008 --> 00:11:59,427
Of course, Master Qifrey.

227
00:11:59,802 --> 00:12:01,304
[bird cawing]

228
00:12:03,014 --> 00:12:04,723
This will be your room.

229
00:12:07,726 --> 00:12:09,978
Apparently Agott's not around.

230
00:12:09,979 --> 00:12:11,355
[COCO] Who's Agott?

231
00:12:11,356 --> 00:12:13,400
[QIFREY]
She's your new roommate.

232
00:12:17,404 --> 00:12:18,613
[Coco exclaims softly]

233
00:12:19,113 --> 00:12:21,781
[QIFREY] There's one workspace,
which you'll share,

234
00:12:21,782 --> 00:12:23,576
and two bedrooms.

235
00:12:23,577 --> 00:12:25,161
[Coco gasps]

236
00:12:25,870 --> 00:12:28,247
[QIFREY] They're down the stairs
in the back.

237
00:12:28,248 --> 00:12:30,166
Don't worry, the doors do lock.

238
00:12:31,084 --> 00:12:33,293
Get some rest if you like.

239
00:12:33,294 --> 00:12:34,961
I had better be on my way.

240
00:12:34,962 --> 00:12:36,923
Call me if you need anything.

241
00:12:39,509 --> 00:12:40,759
[footsteps]

242
00:12:47,392 --> 00:12:49,767
Hello, this is Qifrey.

243
00:12:49,768 --> 00:12:51,395
Coco's settling in nicely.

244
00:12:51,396 --> 00:12:53,732
Thank you for approving
her apprenticeship.

245
00:12:54,899 --> 00:12:56,192
Yes.

246
00:12:56,817 --> 00:12:57,902
No.

247
00:12:58,319 --> 00:12:59,695
Nothing on the book yet.

248
00:12:59,696 --> 00:13:02,240
She may need a bit of time
to get adjusted.

249
00:13:03,199 --> 00:13:04,782
[Coco exclaims]

250
00:13:04,783 --> 00:13:07,954
[COCO] So this is what
a witch's room looks like.

251
00:13:09,289 --> 00:13:11,582
[AGOTT]
That's my side of the desk.

252
00:13:11,583 --> 00:13:13,084
[Coco gasps]

253
00:13:23,219 --> 00:13:25,845
Out of the way. I'm landing.

254
00:13:25,846 --> 00:13:28,015
Oh, I'm sorry.

255
00:13:34,939 --> 00:13:36,566
[exclaims softly]

256
00:13:37,942 --> 00:13:39,401
Nice to meet you!

257
00:13:39,402 --> 00:13:41,946
- Agott, right? I'm Coco...
- I know.

258
00:13:42,405 --> 00:13:44,865
The famous Outsider, right?

259
00:13:45,199 --> 00:13:48,369
I understand you'll be
joining us as an apprentice.

260
00:13:49,245 --> 00:13:50,537
Oh, right.

261
00:13:50,538 --> 00:13:52,665
Sorry to hear
about your mother.

262
00:13:52,666 --> 00:13:54,708
Thanks. That's very kind.

263
00:13:54,709 --> 00:13:56,711
[AGOTT] Because of you...

264
00:13:58,837 --> 00:14:01,674
she'll never be flesh
and blood again, will she?

265
00:14:01,675 --> 00:14:03,049
[Coco inhales sharply]

266
00:14:03,050 --> 00:14:05,679
The reason I'm here
is to save her, if I can.

267
00:14:06,179 --> 00:14:07,722
By becoming a witch...

268
00:14:10,308 --> 00:14:12,184
This is what my life has been.

269
00:14:12,185 --> 00:14:15,187
Drawing casting seals
till my fingers turned black.

270
00:14:15,188 --> 00:14:17,564
Working and working
to pass the tests,

271
00:14:17,565 --> 00:14:20,193
so that one day
I could become an apprentice.

272
00:14:20,819 --> 00:14:23,195
You don't know
the first thing about it.

273
00:14:23,196 --> 00:14:25,113
There's no way
an Outsider like you

274
00:14:25,114 --> 00:14:26,448
will ever be a witch.

275
00:14:26,449 --> 00:14:27,826
♪

276
00:14:29,369 --> 00:14:30,786
No, I don't know.

277
00:14:30,787 --> 00:14:33,080
But I have drawn spells!

278
00:14:33,498 --> 00:14:35,123
I have to at least try!

279
00:14:35,124 --> 00:14:37,334
All right, then prove yourself.

280
00:14:37,335 --> 00:14:38,752
Your test starts tomorrow--

281
00:14:38,753 --> 00:14:40,713
[TETIA] Agott! Coco!

282
00:14:40,714 --> 00:14:42,716
Food time!

283
00:14:43,174 --> 00:14:46,093
- Let's go!
- [stomach growls]

284
00:14:47,804 --> 00:14:49,055
[COCO] Excuse me!

285
00:14:50,557 --> 00:14:52,641
I could eat a Pegasus.

286
00:14:52,642 --> 00:14:53,809
I could, too!

287
00:14:53,810 --> 00:14:56,061
And this will be
Coco's welcome party!

288
00:14:56,062 --> 00:14:58,522
- Such fun!
- Such food.

289
00:14:58,523 --> 00:15:00,107
♪

290
00:15:06,197 --> 00:15:08,490
Normal meal. Ugh.

291
00:15:08,491 --> 00:15:11,786
Um, Master,
where's the welcome party?

292
00:15:12,286 --> 00:15:13,787
No time to prepare.

293
00:15:13,788 --> 00:15:15,790
We'll just have it
some other day.

294
00:15:16,165 --> 00:15:17,207
Where's Agott?

295
00:15:17,208 --> 00:15:19,251
"I'm eating in my room."

296
00:15:19,252 --> 00:15:20,294
It's her choice,

297
00:15:20,587 --> 00:15:23,296
but I do wish she'd join us
every once in a while.

298
00:15:23,297 --> 00:15:26,216
Now, we don't want it
to get cold, do we?

299
00:15:26,217 --> 00:15:27,634
It's your day, Coco.

300
00:15:27,635 --> 00:15:29,344
Would you bless
the meal for us?

301
00:15:29,345 --> 00:15:31,013
[COCO] Oh! Um...

302
00:15:31,930 --> 00:15:33,849
We're grateful for this food.

303
00:15:33,850 --> 00:15:35,518
[ALL] We're grateful
for this food.

304
00:15:41,649 --> 00:15:42,858
[COCO] Mm...

305
00:15:42,859 --> 00:15:44,276
It's so good.

306
00:15:44,277 --> 00:15:45,778
It is, isn't it?

307
00:15:45,779 --> 00:15:47,738
And we bake it ourselves.

308
00:15:47,739 --> 00:15:49,656
Master's an excellent chef.

309
00:15:49,657 --> 00:15:50,867
He is!

310
00:15:51,117 --> 00:15:53,912
It's the locally grown wheat
that makes the difference.

311
00:15:58,082 --> 00:16:00,084
[Coco exclaims softly]

312
00:16:00,627 --> 00:16:02,211
[exclaims]

313
00:16:02,837 --> 00:16:06,172
This area's vegetables
are of superior quality as well.

314
00:16:06,173 --> 00:16:08,675
- [COCO] Thanks! Delicious!
- Thank you, Master Qifrey!

315
00:16:08,676 --> 00:16:09,928
♪

316
00:16:33,576 --> 00:16:35,745
[COCO] Mom... [sniffles]

317
00:16:42,418 --> 00:16:43,878
[birds chirping]

318
00:16:44,337 --> 00:16:46,546
[COCO] So I need
to take tests of some kind

319
00:16:46,547 --> 00:16:48,633
in order to become
an apprentice.

320
00:16:49,175 --> 00:16:51,844
But it sure would be nice
to get some specifics

321
00:16:51,845 --> 00:16:54,220
on what exactly it is
I have to do.

322
00:16:54,221 --> 00:16:55,931
[QIFREY]
Do about what, exactly?

323
00:16:55,932 --> 00:16:57,684
[Coco gasps]

324
00:16:58,392 --> 00:17:01,812
There's a great deal about magic
you won't find in any book.

325
00:17:01,813 --> 00:17:05,273
Trust me, it's best to learn
by doing. So here.

326
00:17:05,274 --> 00:17:06,942
What are they?

327
00:17:06,943 --> 00:17:08,527
Your components,

328
00:17:08,528 --> 00:17:10,571
tools for drawing magic.

329
00:17:11,656 --> 00:17:13,699
Oh, wow!

330
00:17:13,700 --> 00:17:16,452
Amazing!

331
00:17:16,953 --> 00:17:18,162
[gasps]

332
00:17:18,579 --> 00:17:21,915
A pen, just like the wand.

333
00:17:21,916 --> 00:17:24,501
It still scares me to hold this.

334
00:17:24,502 --> 00:17:25,586
But no...

335
00:17:26,337 --> 00:17:29,756
Mom, I'm going to save you
no matter what!

336
00:17:29,757 --> 00:17:32,801
Please, Master Qifrey,
I'm ready to learn!

337
00:17:32,802 --> 00:17:34,971
Good, let's begin.

338
00:17:41,978 --> 00:17:43,729
[QIFREY]
Are you all right, Coco?

339
00:17:43,730 --> 00:17:45,398
Shall we take a break?

340
00:17:46,232 --> 00:17:48,192
[COCO] No. I'm fine.

341
00:17:49,318 --> 00:17:50,528
Very well.

342
00:17:50,737 --> 00:17:52,905
Why don't you sum up
all that you've learned so far?

343
00:17:52,906 --> 00:17:54,532
Sounds good.

344
00:17:55,157 --> 00:17:57,325
Let's see, to start with,

345
00:17:57,326 --> 00:17:59,453
a spell is composed
of three elements.

346
00:18:00,162 --> 00:18:02,248
The sigil lies in the center.

347
00:18:02,623 --> 00:18:05,667
It's surrounded by
markings called signs.

348
00:18:05,668 --> 00:18:08,795
And then, the outer circle
that completes it,

349
00:18:08,796 --> 00:18:10,296
that's called the ring.

350
00:18:10,297 --> 00:18:12,717
The types of sigil are Fire,

351
00:18:13,091 --> 00:18:14,343
Water,

352
00:18:14,969 --> 00:18:16,220
Light,

353
00:18:16,470 --> 00:18:17,805
and Wind.

354
00:18:18,222 --> 00:18:21,225
They determine
what kind of magic it is.

355
00:18:21,517 --> 00:18:25,562
The signs determine what form
the magic ultimately takes,

356
00:18:25,563 --> 00:18:28,357
as well as its size
and direction.

357
00:18:29,776 --> 00:18:33,236
Lastly, when the outer ring
is completed,

358
00:18:33,237 --> 00:18:36,282
that locks the seal in place
and activates the spell.

359
00:18:36,783 --> 00:18:39,451
Memorizing all this is
really taking it out of me.

360
00:18:39,452 --> 00:18:41,621
But you explained it,
that's what counts!

361
00:18:43,081 --> 00:18:45,874
Right. I'm going to try
drawing one now!

362
00:18:45,875 --> 00:18:48,294
Good for you! That's the spirit!

363
00:18:50,797 --> 00:18:52,840
[Coco sighs]

364
00:18:53,967 --> 00:18:55,509
[Coco sighs]

365
00:18:56,886 --> 00:18:58,972
[Coco exclaims softly]

366
00:19:01,265 --> 00:19:02,515
[QIFREY] Uh?

367
00:19:02,516 --> 00:19:04,101
- [Coco grunts]
- [Qifrey gasps]

368
00:19:04,102 --> 00:19:06,103
- [QIFREY] Don't throw it away.
- [gasps]

369
00:19:06,104 --> 00:19:08,814
No! Please don't look!

370
00:19:08,815 --> 00:19:11,316
It's not even worthy
of your attention!

371
00:19:11,317 --> 00:19:12,693
It's sloppy,

372
00:19:12,819 --> 00:19:15,361
and the lines are all wobbly,
and it's a great big mess.

373
00:19:15,362 --> 00:19:17,238
Of course it is.

374
00:19:17,239 --> 00:19:18,991
You're only just learning.

375
00:19:18,992 --> 00:19:22,244
To that end, here's something
you may want to look at.

376
00:19:22,870 --> 00:19:25,580
See this spot?
Your ring doesn't fully connect.

377
00:19:25,581 --> 00:19:28,875
Unless the circle is complete,
the spell won't activate.

378
00:19:28,876 --> 00:19:30,168
[COCO] Oh.

379
00:19:32,088 --> 00:19:34,006
[QIFREY]
It's natural to be unsteady

380
00:19:34,007 --> 00:19:35,799
when you're getting used
to something new.

381
00:19:35,800 --> 00:19:38,551
You're like a foal
that's just learning to stand.

382
00:19:38,552 --> 00:19:40,137
Don't you worry.

383
00:19:40,138 --> 00:19:42,682
You'll be running wild
in no time at all.

384
00:19:44,266 --> 00:19:48,146
Now, connect the lines,
and activate the spell.

385
00:20:00,867 --> 00:20:02,117
- [Coco screams]
- [Qifrey gasps]

386
00:20:02,118 --> 00:20:03,409
I am so sorry!

387
00:20:03,410 --> 00:20:05,163
It was an accident!
I didn't mean to!

388
00:20:06,372 --> 00:20:08,081
[Coco screams]

389
00:20:08,082 --> 00:20:09,875
[COCO] I am
so, so, so, so sorry.

390
00:20:09,876 --> 00:20:12,794
Let me dry it off. [pants]

391
00:20:12,795 --> 00:20:14,546
- Is it working?
- [QIFREY] Settle down, Coco!

392
00:20:14,547 --> 00:20:15,714
Apologies, Agott.

393
00:20:15,715 --> 00:20:16,924
- Are you all right?
- [COCO] Better?

394
00:20:18,634 --> 00:20:20,343
Perfectly fine.

395
00:20:20,344 --> 00:20:22,763
I'm really not bothered
in the least.

396
00:20:23,389 --> 00:20:26,391
But may I ask for a look
at the casting seal she drew?

397
00:20:26,392 --> 00:20:28,310
[QIFREY] Oh, yes.

398
00:20:29,436 --> 00:20:31,521
[AGOTT] Ah, here's the problem.

399
00:20:31,522 --> 00:20:32,857
[Coco exclaims softly]

400
00:20:36,194 --> 00:20:37,527
[AGOTT] Look...

401
00:20:37,528 --> 00:20:40,446
This sign is longer
than the others.

402
00:20:40,447 --> 00:20:43,158
It amplified the pressure
in this direction,

403
00:20:43,159 --> 00:20:45,243
causing the water
to come gushing out.

404
00:20:45,703 --> 00:20:49,331
[QIFREY] Well done!
Astutely observed, as always.

405
00:20:49,540 --> 00:20:50,958
[Qifrey sighs]

406
00:20:51,249 --> 00:20:53,543
Yes, she should be in
very good hands with you.

407
00:20:53,544 --> 00:20:54,628
[COCO] Huh?

408
00:20:59,759 --> 00:21:01,509
For the next few days,

409
00:21:01,510 --> 00:21:04,096
I'm going to be away
visiting the Great Hall.

410
00:21:04,097 --> 00:21:05,138
While I'm gone,

411
00:21:05,139 --> 00:21:07,515
do look after her,
won't you, Agott?

412
00:21:07,516 --> 00:21:09,475
I will. Of course.

413
00:21:09,476 --> 00:21:10,519
[door opens]

414
00:21:10,895 --> 00:21:12,145
Wait! Hold on!

415
00:21:12,146 --> 00:21:14,731
One may learn much indeed
from their peers.

416
00:21:14,732 --> 00:21:17,567
You'll see. Watch her closely
and take it all in.

417
00:21:17,568 --> 00:21:19,069
[Coco gasps]

418
00:21:19,070 --> 00:21:21,530
But, Master, I...

419
00:21:21,906 --> 00:21:23,950
[door closes]

420
00:21:25,492 --> 00:21:28,245
Um, I am sorry
about before. I never--

421
00:21:28,246 --> 00:21:30,538
I said I wasn't bothered,
didn't I?

422
00:21:30,539 --> 00:21:32,332
So you can stop apologizing.

423
00:21:33,793 --> 00:21:36,086
- More importantly...
- [gasps]

424
00:21:36,087 --> 00:21:38,546
I told you to prove yourself,

425
00:21:38,547 --> 00:21:40,339
and I intend to make you.

426
00:21:40,340 --> 00:21:41,382
As of now,

427
00:21:41,383 --> 00:21:43,635
the cushy little lessons
are over.

428
00:21:43,636 --> 00:21:46,346
And your test has begun.

429
00:21:47,305 --> 00:21:48,766
[COCO] What...

430
00:21:52,519 --> 00:21:54,230
♪

431
00:22:06,075 --> 00:22:08,368
[♪ closing theme song playing]

